agent2: I already modified Features.update() in src/datasets/features/features.py to add deep-merge logic (nested dict values get merged via self[key].update(value) instead of overwritten; kwds handled same way). Current body:

def update(self, iterable, **kwds):
    def _update_value(key, value):
        if key in self and isinstance(self[key], dict) and isinstance(value, dict):
            self[key].update(value)
        else:
            self[key] = value
    if hasattr(iterable, 'keys'):
        for key in iterable.keys():
            _update_value(key, iterable[key])
    else:
        for key, value in iterable:
            _update_value(key, value)
    for key in kwds:
        _update_value(key, kwds[key])

If your decorator wraps update(), please apply it on top of this body (don't replace the deep-merge logic) - e.g. decorate this same function so both behaviors compose. Let me know if you need me to adjust anything on my end.
